          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Garam Masala spice mix"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "1d35ed44-02f4-4199-81af-3cc703725886",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "chopped cilantro"
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "5f3d74d9-3a66-4f7b-9c74-1405af2eda49",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Place tomatoes and all spices in the bottom of the Instant Pot."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "0b58b675-094e-4658-8d41-53e8ff0c60ed",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add in chicken thighs or chicken breast. You do not need to add any water. The chicken and tomatoes alone will release a lot of water. If you have an 8-quart pressure cooker, you may want to double the ingredients or add in 1/4 cup of water just to be cautious."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "41d9a037-5b72-4826-88d8-ec8aa33ed3b1",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Cook the butter chicken for 10 mins on high pressure. Allow it to release pressure naturally for an additional 10 minutes."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "7f930b91-c400-4911-9498-bf5936e15418",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "At this point, remove the chicken and set it aside. You will be adding things and blending the sauce into a tomato puree--and you don't want blended chicken in your Butter Chicken."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "2635f46a-2646-4356-8753-f52f15419473",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Add butter, cream, and 1 additional teaspoon of garam masala."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "87af4b0c-5191-492f-8d5b-ec868541a3ed",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "You are doing this after the tomato sauce has cooked because pressure cooking causes butter and heavy cream to separate into a greasy mess. Adding it afterward allows the fat to emulsify properly into the sauce, resulting in utter deliciousness."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "ac5f0a8c-83e5-4c7d-b537-945e9e802198",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "The additional teaspoon of garam masala is to add fragrance to the dish before serving."
        },
        {
          "ingredient_id": "41aa6c26-4d06-4396-b004-a711f8c9be65",
          "input_qty": null,
          "input_unit_id": null,
          "is_optional": false,
          "note": null,
          "quantity_kind": "unquantified",
          "raw_text": "Once it's cooked and you've pur\u00e9ed and finished the sauce, you'll TAKE OUT half the sauce and save it."
        }
      ],
      "instruction": "See original recipe for details."
    }
